title: For Sale:  M4 Survival Rifle
postcontent: The M4 Survival Rifle was a .22 calibre bolt-action rifle developed during WW2 as part of the survival gear stored under the seat of American military aircraft. It was designed to give downed aircrew a survival weapon for foraging wild game for food.The M4 was developed from the H-R bolt-action M265 sporting rifle, adapted to a sheet metal frame with telescoping wire butt stock, a 14-inch NOW 16-inch....detachable barrel chambered for .22 Hornet and the 4 shot detachable box magazine of the Savage Stevens M23D .22 Hornet sporting rifle. The M4 weighs approximately four pounds and with barrel detached and telescoping stock closed makes a ~14 inch overall package. Due to the possible use of the M4 by downed aircrew as a combat weapon, military issue ammunition in .22 Hornet is loaded with Full Metal Jacket to comply with the hague convention barring use of expanding bullets in warfare. 1 box uopened Military Will Ship to FFL......
